\citation{drautz2019ace}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Cross-domain comparison of data cleaning vs.\ architecture improvement. In three strong-feature domains (AlN, CIFAR-10, DrugBank), the relative performance improvement from SCX-based data cleaning (blue) exceeds that from switching model architectures (orange) by a factor of 11--19. On DermaMNIST, where low-resolution thumbnails provide weak features, both improvements are small---consistent with the theoretical weak-feature bound. Error bars show 95\% confidence intervals over 5 random training seeds.}}{4}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:cross_domain}{{1}{4}{Cross-domain comparison of data cleaning vs.\ architecture improvement. In three strong-feature domains (AlN, CIFAR-10, DrugBank), the relative performance improvement from SCX-based data cleaning (blue) exceeds that from switching model architectures (orange) by a factor of 11--19. On DermaMNIST, where low-resolution thumbnails provide weak features, both improvements are small---consistent with the theoretical weak-feature bound. Error bars show 95\% confidence intervals over 5 random training seeds}{figure.1}{}}
