\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Feature strength ($f_{\max }$, the maximum pairwise feature correlation coefficient) versus the SCX noise detection test error across all four domains. The linear correlation is $r = 0.966$, indicating that feature quality almost entirely determines SCX performance, independent of domain or model architecture. The dashed line shows the least-squares fit.}}{6}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:fmax}{{3}{6}{Feature strength ($f_{\max }$, the maximum pairwise feature correlation coefficient) versus the SCX noise detection test error across all four domains. The linear correlation is $r = 0.966$, indicating that feature quality almost entirely determines SCX performance, independent of domain or model architecture. The dashed line shows the least-squares fit}{figure.3}{}}
